OL,3,CMum of girl killed by drink-drug
OL,4,Cdriver calls for blood-testing law
OL,5,Cchange
OL,7,FThe driver of the car spent 11 weeks
OL,8,Fin a coma. Police had taken a sample
OL,9,Fof his blood, but told Sharlotte's
OL,10,Ffamily they weren't able to test it
OL,11,Funtil they had his consent - leaving
OL,12,Fthem grieving and without answers.
OL,14,FUnder current legislation, blood
OL,15,Fsamples can be taken if someone is
OL,16,Funconscious and has been involved in a
OL,17,Ffatal collision. However, a sample
OL,18,Fcannot be tested for evidence of
OL,19,Fdriving under the influence without
OL,20,Ftheir consent.
