OL,7,FShe added: "Especially for an
OL,8,Finvestigation, it just puts everything
OL,9,Fon hold and you think I'm never going
OL,10,Fto get there, I'm never going to know."
OL,12,FOnce the driver was conscious, he did
OL,13,Fconsent to having his blood tested. It
OL,14,Fwas found to contain almost twice the
OL,15,Flegal limit of alcohol, as well as
OL,16,Fcocaine.
OL,18,FHe was later jailed, but Sharlotte's
OL,19,Fmother said the decision on when to
OL,20,Ftest his blood shouldn't have rested
OL,21,Fwith him.
