OL,7,FThe campaign was mentioned in The
OL,8,FCommons today after Deputy Chair of
OL,9,Fthe Conservative Party, Jonathan
OL,10,FGullis, introduced a Bill he referred
OL,11,Fto as "Sharlotte's law".
OL,13,FMr Gullis' Road Traffic (Testing of
OL,14,FBlood) Bill would amend section 7A of
OL,15,Fthe Road Traffic Act 1988 to allow a
OL,16,Fblood sample to be tested without the
OL,17,Fconsent of the person it was taken
OL,18,Ffrom.
