OL,7,FA Department for Transport
OL,8,FSpokesperson said: "Every death on our
OL,9,Froads is a tragedy and we extend our
OL,10,Fdeepest sympathies to Sharlotte-Sky
OL,11,FNaglis' family and friends.
OL,13,F"While we do keep such matters under
OL,14,Freview, driving under the influence is
OL,15,Falready regarded as completely
OL,16,Funacceptable, with tough penalties in
OL,17,Fplace including a lifetime ban on
OL,18,Fdriving and 14 years to life in prison
OL,19,Ffor those who cause death by dangerous
OL,20,Fdriving."
